# Reproduce the multi-output serde architecture and storage bench
# from the LMCache serde-multi-output-extensions branch.
#
# Scope: lmcache only.  Skips vllm + flashinfer entirely (the
# multi-output serde is pure Python; no CUDA kernel build needed).
#
# Stages:
#   00_doctor                 — basic env check
#   01_fetch_repos            — clone mcgrof/LMCache@serde-multi-output-extensions
#   04_build_lmcache          — pip install -e .  (skips C-ext build via env hint)
#   s_serdes_unit_tests       — pytest tests/v1/distributed/serde/
#   s_serdes_storage_bench    — Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct shaped storage bench
#                               on the user-supplied NVMe path
#   11_report                 — JSON summary
#
# Lanes gated by the bench (all four are MANDATORY; missing any one
# fails the run with a coverage error):
#   bf16_baseline   raw fp16 K + V (reference)
#   sym_fp8         upstream LMCache Fp8QuantizationSerializer shape
#   asym_k16_v8     Mode 1 / all-NVMe (paper Eq. 3, 0.75x FP16)
#   asym_v_only     Mode 2 / split-tier (paper Eq. 4, 0.25x FP16,
#                   = 1/3 of Mode 1; K stays in CPU-pinned host RAM)
#
# The bench also gates the unit tests for both modes
# (test_asym_k16_v8_multi.py + test_asym_k16_v8_v_only.py) — a stale
# CONFIG_KNLP_LMCACHE_REF that predates Mode 2's bc0d5873 commit on
# serde-multi-output-extensions fails the unit-test stage with an
# actionable error.
#
# Storage path resolution:
#   CONFIG_KNLP_NVME_PATH > KNLP_NVME_PATH env > tmpdir inside run_dir
#
# The bench always also runs against /dev/shm (tmpfs) as a RAM
# upper-bound so codec cost is separable from storage cost.
#
# Setup of the NVMe mount itself is left to the user.  The stage
# does not mkfs / mount / format — it writes into whatever path is
# configured.  Document the underlying device, filesystem, and mount
# options separately when reporting absolute throughput numbers.
#
# Usage:
#
#   make defconfig-decode-serdes
#   cat >> .config << 'EOF'
#   CONFIG_KNLP_NVME_PATH="/mnt/my-nvme/serdes-bench"
#   CONFIG_KNLP_STORAGE_DEVICE_LABEL="micron_7400_894g"
#   EOF
#   make
#
# On a RunPod / Prime Intellect pod where there is no controlled
# NVMe (the container disk is overlayfs on the host's storage),
# leave CONFIG_KNLP_NVME_PATH empty.  The stage falls back to a
# tmpdir under the run directory and emits a warning that absolute
# throughput is container-stack dependent; the byte-ratio claims
# (sym fp8 = 0.5x, asym K16/V8 = 0.75x) are still validated.
#
# Estimated runtime: 5-10 min total (pip install + 17 pytest tests
# + 72-cell bench sweep).  GPU not required.
CONFIG_KNLP_REPRODUCE_DECODE=y
CONFIG_KNLP_REPRODUCE_PROFILE="decode-serdes"
CONFIG_KNLP_WORKTREE_ROOT=".."
CONFIG_KNLP_RESULTS_ROOT="./results/decode-serdes"
CONFIG_KNLP_BUILD_ROOT="./build/decode"
# vllm + flashinfer not needed for the serdes-multi-output bench.
CONFIG_KNLP_VLLM_REPO=""
CONFIG_KNLP_VLLM_REF=""
CONFIG_KNLP_VLLM_DIR="vllm"
CONFIG_KNLP_FLASHINFER_REPO=""
CONFIG_KNLP_FLASHINFER_REF=""
CONFIG_KNLP_FLASHINFER_DIR="flashinfer"
CONFIG_KNLP_LMCACHE_REPO="https://github.com/mcgrof/LMCache.git"
CONFIG_KNLP_LMCACHE_REF="serde-multi-output-extensions"
CONFIG_KNLP_LMCACHE_DIR="lmcache"
# NVMe mount point for the bench.  Override per device-under-test;
# leave empty to fall back to a tmpdir (still validates byte ratios
# and round-trip quality, but absolute throughput is container-stack
# dependent and not portable).
CONFIG_KNLP_NVME_PATH=""
# Human-readable storage device label for result comparison.
CONFIG_KNLP_STORAGE_DEVICE_LABEL=""
CONFIG_KNLP_ENABLE_WANDB=n
CONFIG_KNLP_ENABLE_TRACKERIO=n
CONFIG_KNLP_UPLOAD_ARTIFACTS=n
CONFIG_KNLP_ALLOW_HARDWARE_SKIPS=y
CONFIG_KNLP_FAIL_ON_DIRTY_GIT=y
CONFIG_KNLP_REQUIRE_PINNED_REFS=n
